content.rendered:
I went for a stroll along the regent’s canal and came upon a strange and motley parade. Following a barge with a papier-mâché queen’s head fixed to its prow, hundreds of revellers took to the water in decorated rubber dinghies while others (myself included) danced alongside.

I also took some photos with my phone.
